			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Parse Forest Diagnostics with Dr. Ambiguity</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/HendrikusJSBasten.html">Hendrikus J. S. Basten</a>, <a href="../profile/JurgenVinju.html">Jurgen Vinju</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_16">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_16</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagM">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It analyzes language descriptions (grammars/parsers) by diagnosing ambiguity in parse forests.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> Dr. Ambiguity is a dedicated tool supporting this diagnostic workflow.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The setting is grounded in grammar formalisms and generalized parsing infrastructure.
</li></ul></li></ul>
